President Obama has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key Administration posts. Kimberly Owens, a Realtor from Phoenix, Arizona, will be appointed as a member of the Board of Trustees of the Christopher Columbus Fellowship Foundation. Sima F. Sarrafan, a Senior Attorney at Microsoft, will also be appointed as a member of the Board of Trustees of the Christopher Columbus Fellowship Foundation. Jan R. Frye, the Deputy Assistant Secretary for Acquisition and Logistics for the Department of Veterans Affairs, will be appointed as a member of the Committee for Purchase from People Who Are Blind or Severely Disabled. Dr. Carol E. Lowman, the Deputy Director of the U.S. Army Contracting Command, will also be appointed as a member of the Committee for Purchase from People Who Are Blind or Severely Disabled. These individuals are seen as valuable additions to the Administration as they work to address the challenges facing America.